China has told Hong Kong its next leader will be selected <a href="http://qz.com/258189/what-macaus-election-says-about-the-future-of-hong-kong/" target="_blank">via an election committee in 2017</a>—dashing the <a href="http://qz.com/257540/hong-kongs-battle-with-china-over-democracy-begins-in-earnest-this-weekend/">aspirations of pro-democracy activists</a>. On Sunday, Macau re-elected its chief executive similarly, in a vote where Fernando Chui was the only candidate. The process took 25 minutes.

